#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:5.1"
msgid "16. Anupakhajjasikkhāpada"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 16: the training rule on encroaching"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.16.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.247"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa415"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.2"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: vuṭṭhāpenti → ettha te iti kammapadaṃ ūnaṃ viya
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū varaseyyāyo palibundhenti, therā bhikkhū vuṭṭhāpenti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six had taken possession of the best sleeping places, but the senior monks made them move."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.4"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr "They thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.5"
msgid "“kena nu kho mayaṃ upāyena idheva vassaṃ vaseyyāmā”ti?"
msgstr "“What can we do so that we may dwell here during the rainy season?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.6"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū there bhikkhū anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappenti—"
msgstr "They then arranged their sleeping places in a way that encroached on the senior monks, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.7"
msgid "“yassa sambādho bhavissati so pakkamissatī”ti."
msgstr "“Those who feel crowded will leave.”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.8"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.9"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:6.10"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū there bhikkhū anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six arrange their sleeping places in a way that encroaches upon the senior monks?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.43"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa416"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways,  they told the Master.…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:7.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, there bhikkhū anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:7.3"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:7.4"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:7.5"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, there bhikkhū anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you arrange your sleeping places in a way that encroaches on the senior monks?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.248"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:7.6"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:7.7"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:8.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa417"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
#. VAR: pubbupagataṃ → pubbūpagataṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: anupakhajja → anūpakhajja (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:8.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu saṃghike vihāre jānaṃ pubbupagataṃ bhikkhuṃ anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappeyya—"
msgstr "‘If, in a dwelling belonging to the Order, a monk arranges his sleeping place in a way that encroaches on a monk that he knows arrived there before him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:8.3"
msgid "yassa sambādho bhavissati so pakkamissatī’ti, etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññaṃ, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "with the intention that anyone who feels crowded will leave, and he does so only for this reason and no other, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:8.4"
msgid "(<em>16</em>:<strong>65</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:9.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.16.2"></a>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.16.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa418"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:9.2"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:9.3"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:9.4"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:9.5"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:9.6"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa419"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:10.1"
msgid "Saṃghiko nāma"
msgstr "A dwelling belonging to the Order:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:10.2"
msgid "vihāro saṃghassa dinno hoti pariccatto."
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa420"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:11.1"
msgid "Jānāti nāma"
msgstr "He knows:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:11.2"
msgid "vuḍḍhoti jānāti, gilānoti jānāti, saṃghena dinnoti jānāti."
msgstr "he knows that he is senior, he knows that he is sick, he knows that it was given to him by the Order."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa421"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:12.1"
msgid "Anupakhajjāti"
msgstr "Encroaches on:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:12.2"
msgid "anupavisitvā."
msgstr "enters after."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa422"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:13.1"
msgid "Seyyaṃ kappeyyāti"
msgstr "Arranges his sleeping place:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:13.2"
msgid "mañcassa vā pīṭhassa vā pavisantassa vā nikkhamantassa vā upacāre seyyaṃ santharati vā santharāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "if he puts out his sleeping place in the vicinity of the bed, the bench, the entry way, or the departure way, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:13.3"
msgid "Abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa423"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:14.1"
msgid "Etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññanti"
msgstr "He does so only for this reason and no other:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:14.2"
msgid "na añño koci paccayo hoti anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappetuṃ."
msgstr "there is no other reason for arranging the sleeping place in a way that encroaches."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:15.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.16.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa424"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:15.2"
msgid "Saṃghike saṃghikasaññī anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:15.3"
msgid "Saṃghike vematiko anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:15.4"
msgid "Saṃghike puggalikasaññī anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa425"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.249"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:16.1"
msgid "Mañcassa vā pīṭhassa vā pavisantassa vā nikkhamantassa vā upacāraṃ ṭhapetvā seyyaṃ santharati vā santharāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he puts out his sleeping place, or gets it put out, anywhere apart from the vicinity of the bed, the bench, the entry way, or the departure way, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:16.2"
msgid "Abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:16.3"
msgid "Vihārassa upacāre vā upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ vā maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā ajjhokāse vā seyyaṃ santharati vā santharāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he puts out his sleeping place, or gets it put out, in the vicinity of a dwelling, in an assembly-hall, under a roof-cover, at the foot of a tree, or out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:16.4"
msgid "Abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:16.5"
msgid "Puggalike saṃghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:16.6"
msgid "Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:16.7"
msgid "Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:16.8"
msgid "Attano puggalike anāpatti."
msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:17.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.16.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa426"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:17.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:17.3"
msgid "gilāno pavisati,"
msgstr "if he enters because he is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:17.4"
msgid "sītena vā uṇhena vā pīḷito pavisati,"
msgstr "if he enters because he is feeling cold or hot;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:17.5"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:17.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:17.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa427"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc16:18.1"
msgid "Anupakhajjasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on encroaching, is finished."

